The article is a statement by the Commander in Chief of the United States, celebrating the 242nd birthday of the United States Navy. The statement acknowledges the bravery and service of generations of men and women who have served in the Navy, projecting American power on the seas, land, and in the air. The Navy continues to deter enemies and confront threats from terrorists and rogue nations. The statement also emphasizes the duty to support service members, military families, and veterans. The commissioning of the USS Gerald R. Ford earlier this year is highlighted as a symbol of the nation's commitment to providing the military with the necessary tools and technology. The statement concludes with a salute to American heroes and a blessing for the men and women of the Navy and all Armed Forces.